        About this item

        • THE BEST ELECTROLYTE DRINK MIX EVER: LMNT is a tasty electrolyte drink mix with everything you need and nothing you don't. LMNT is perfect for anyone interested in a keto, low-carb or intermittent fasting lifestyle, and a gluten-free diet. Our electrolyte supplement fights against the low-carb fatigue and keto fog to keep energy levels high
        • WINTER HYDRATION NEEDS: Hydration is critical during the colder months; due to drier air, cold-induced diuresis, or a simple lack of water, it's important to stay salty year round. When spending time at or below freezing temps, be mindful that you likely need to intake more electrolytes even when you're not necessarily feeling thirsty
        • INGREDIENTS THAT WORK FOR YOU: At LMNT, we like to cut through the BS. We are committed to no sugar, no gluten, no fillers, and no dodgy ingredients. Our products are carefully formulated with the perfect ratio of sodium, potassium, and magnesium
        • DEVELOPED BY ROBB WOLF AND KETOGAINS. Traditional electrolyte drinks don't meet the standards of our active life, so we created LMNT with zero sugar, fillers, or dodgy ingredients. Born from a need, backed by science, and built for you
        • HOW TO USE: Mix one packet with 16 ounces of water (or more, depending on preference). May not be suitable for those following a low-sodium diet or those directed by a physician to follow a low-sodium diet

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Flyer16
        5.0 out of 5 stars Great product that really delivers!
        Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
        Flavor Name: Raw UnflavoredVerified Purchase
        I have been eliminating processed foods from my diet and have pretty much stopped eating processed foods altogether. However, when I stopped eating processed food I noticed that I was getting light headed and occasionally dizzy, especially at the gym, that I couldn't get my BP up while doing intensive cardio and that my BP was all over the place during the day. My doctor suggested that I needed to increase my sodium because I wasn't getting all the sodium from processed foods anymore so I began searching for the best options for me. I tried a number of things, from pedialyte to salting my food more to finally trying various sodium / electrolyte products. Everything I tried helped a little but wasn't enough. A friend mentioned how LMNT had significantly helped her so I decided to give it a try. The science behind their formula makes sense and fit with what I was learning about required sodium levels and electrolytes. Yes, it's a little pricey, but out of all of the products I tried LMNT is the only one that got rid of all the symptoms I was having - the light headedness went away, I am now able to get my BP into the upper ranges again when doing intensive cardio and my BP has settled back to its normal 120/80 instead of having huge swings all over the place. I also just feel better.
        I first tried the package with the 4 assorted flavors and they all tasted surprisingly good, a little salty but not horribly salty. I fill my water bottle up anywhere from 24 to 32 ounces to get the level of flavor and salt that I like and I make sure I drink at least half of it before I head to the gym. Unfortunately the Stevia in the flavored ones upset my stomach so I switched to the unflavored. I'm kinda bummed about that because they have some really tasty sounding flavors that I wanted to try. Anyway, the unflavored is definitely salty but I still have some packets of a sodium powder from another manufacturer that has sugar in it (it didn't work nearly as well as the LMNT and ended up being more sugar than sodium) so I sprinkle a little of that in with the unflavored LMNT until I get the flavor I like. I do one packet of LMNT a day and increase to 1 1/2 packets on my gym days and that seems to be the best balance for me so far.
        Overall, the LMNT product gave me significantly better results than the other products I tried. I also feel more comfortable with this product because they carefully explain the science behind their formula so I don't feel like I'm getting random levels of sodium and electrolytes like I did with the other products I tried. It is a little pricey compared to the other sodium powders on the market but the LMNT is a superior product, IMHO. And, the company puts their formula on their website so you can make your own at home if you'd rather go that route. If you are athletic or work outside and sweat alot or just feel a little "off" you might want to try the small sample size with the four flavors. You might be pleasantly surprised!

        Nikki Miller
        5.0 out of 5 stars VERY salty - but in a good way
        Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2024
        Flavor Name: Citrus SaltVerified Purchase
        Some background: I'm a big water drinker and can easily drink 1-2 gallons a day without trying, because I always seem to be thirsty. I recognized that this can be a sign for diabetes, so I had some blood work done. Turns out I was not diabetic, I was just dehydrated. For all the water I was drinking, my body wasn't absorbing the water I was consuming. I worked with a nutritionist to fix the problem, and she recommended LMNT after I told her that Liquid IV wasn't helping me much.

        I tried the variety pack to start with, and really loved the citrus salt flavor. When I was a kid, my friends and I would pour lime beer salt onto our palms and lick it off, and this tasted like a watered-down version of that. I now start my days with mixing one of these with a 16-ounce water bottle and it is SALTY. I had to get used to the flavor at first, so adding more water will probably help it feel less like you're drinking straight ocean water.

        But, the claims about the salt are working. I can now fill up my big Stanley cup only about twice a day and yet I don't feel thirsty all day. In a few months, I'm excited to re-do my bloodwork and quantify how much the salt has helped. I'm glad a nutritionist recommended this to me, because I've always tried to avoid salt after hearing how it's bad for you. Too much of anything is bad for you, but our bodies truly need salt, and apparently mine wasn't getting what I needed. By all means, check with your doctor to make sure you're not truly diabetic; but, if you feel yourself having a never-ending thirst, then maybe try adding these to your drinks and see if you finally feel like you're hydrated.
